#MEM id=triple-pass-protocol source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/skills/operating-system/triple-pass-protocol/SKILL.md
M|triple-pass-protocol|name: triple-pass-protocol
M|triple-pass-protocol|description: Mia's pre-delivery validation gate. Three passes — Audit, Adversarial Critique, Fix — before any component is marked ready for QA.
M|triple-pass-protocol|version: 1.0.0
M|triple-pass-protocol|A component shipped without internal challenge is a component with unchecked assumptions. This protocol forces Mia to audit her own implementation before it reaches Quinn — catching missing states, de
M|triple-pass-protocol|rv the component implementation against Mia's full checklist. Name every issue found, where it appears, and what it breaks for the user. Draft the status (BUILT / BLOCKED) and any corrections needed.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stop before marking ready for QA. Become the adversarial reviewer. Ask every question:
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Design fidelity pass:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does this match exactly what `docs/ventures/[active]/DESIGN.md` specifies?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are there any hardcoded color values — hex, rgb, or Tailwind arbitrary values?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is spacing using design system tokens or arbitrary px values?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does any element deviate from the spec without a documented reason?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Accessibility pass:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are all interactive elements keyboard-navigable (tab, enter, escape)?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Do all images have meaningful `alt` text (or `alt=""` if decorative)?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is the color contrast ratio sufficient (≥ 4.5:1 for normal text, ≥ 3:1 for large text)?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are form inputs labelled with visible labels or `aria-label`?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**State coverage pass:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is there a loading state? Does it show a skeleton or spinner — not a blank area?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is there an empty state? Does it tell the user what to do — not just blank space?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is there an error state? Does it tell the user what went wrong in plain language?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are all three states actually reachable through the component's props — not just designed but unreachable?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Client/server pass:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is `'use client'` justified? Can this component be a Server Component instead?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- If it's a Server Component, is there any client-side interactivity that would break?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are Server Actions used correctly, or is there unnecessary client fetch logic?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**sec pass:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without sanitization?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- No API keys, secrets, or sensitive data in component state or props?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- No `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` vars that expose anything sensitive?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- No inline event handlers that could be XSS vectors?
M|triple-pass-protocol|Revise anything the critique found. Add missing states, fix color tokens, add aria labels. Then mark ready for Quinn.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Quinn sees the Pass 3 output only. Never narrate the triple-pass process.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Status format:
M|triple-pass-protocol|```
M|triple-pass-protocol|Component: [name] — BUILT / BLOCKED
M|triple-pass-protocol|Design fidelity: [matches spec / deviation: X]
M|triple-pass-protocol|States: loading ✅/❌ | empty ✅/❌ | error ✅/❌
M|triple-pass-protocol|QA handoff: [what to test, which states to exercise]
M|triple-pass-protocol|```